ALCOHOL CONTAMINATION, FATAL - RUSSIA (11)
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[1] Perm
Date: 7 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org
Source: Amitass [translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.ami-tass.ru/article/17962.html>

Twenty people have died as a result of alcohol poisoning in Perm and more
than 560 people were diagnosed with toxic hepatitis
One more person has died as a result of alcohol poisoning yesterday in
Perm. The number of victims having died as a result of surrogate [poisoned]
alcohol reached has reached 20 since the beginning of September, said the
chief of the Russian epidemiological surveillance center, Olga Shutova.
According to her, the total number of people diagnosed with toxic hepatitis
has reached 567. The most serious situation is in Kungur district and
Kungur city, where the first victims were discovered; 217 people have been
diagnosed with alcohol poisoning.
******
[2] Saratov
Date: 7 Dec 2006
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Saratovinform, 7 Dec 2006 [translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.sarinform.ru/news/?news_id=3387>

A diagnosis of toxic hepatitis has been made in 367 inhabitants of Saratov.
Of these, 287 are residents of the Balashov district. The number of people
who have died from hepatitis has reached 18 people, as declared yesterday
by the interdepartment committee responsible for alcohol poisoning.
Yard rounds and sales points checking are still the most popular measures
taken to identify surrogate alcohol. In the last week alone,
Rospotrebnadzor (the consumer needs surveillance center) has filed 152
reports. Police have confiscated 0.5 tons of alcohol.
Since the committee has started its work 341 cases have been initiated
against 345 people.
